math_problem.A99:
Let $f: \mathbb{N} \rightarrow \mathbb{N}$ be a function satisfying the following conditions:
(1) $f(1)=1$;
(2) $\forall n\in \mathbb{N}$, $3f(n) f(2n+1) =f(2n) ( 1+3f(n) )$;
(3) $\forall n\in \mathbb{N}$, $f(2n) < 6 f(n)$.
Find all solutions of equation $f(k) +f(l)=293$, where $k<l$.
($\mathbb{N}$ denotes the set of all natural numbers). Instead of determining all pairs of natural numbers $k < l$ whose images under $f$ sum to the specified total, simply find $t = f(47) - 278$, where $f(47)$ is the value of the function at $47$ derived from the recursive relations.

